    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture indicates heightened activity across multiple theaters. In the Middle East, the deployment of USS Tripoli and the presence of USS Gerald R. Ford and USS Abraham Lincoln carrier strike groups underscore the escalating tensions with Iran. The recent fire aboard USS Gerald R. Ford highlights the operational challenges faced by U.S. forces in the region. The deployment of USS Mustin to Japan reflects a strategic shift in the Pacific, replacing the last forward-deployed cruiser, USS Robert Smalls. The Arctic Edge 2026 exercise demonstrates a focus on improving readiness and interoperability in the Arctic region, with significant air activity involving C30J and E3TF aircraft. The Strait of Hormuz remains a critical flashpoint, with multiple commercial ships damaged in suspected Iranian attacks, indicating a volatile maritime environment. Overall, the data suggests a strategic emphasis on deterring Iranian aggression, maintaining a strong presence in the Pacific, and enhancing Arctic capabilities.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
